      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the wedges have had an initial 10 min, remove the tray[s] from the oven and add the<strong> red onion wedges </strong>with <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), then add a small drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and mix everything together</p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for 12-15 min or until everything is tender – these are your <strong>berbere vegetables</strong></p><p>While the vegetables are cooking, cut your <strong>green chilli[es]</strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop roughly</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1682100172950-x200.jpg",
