            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>coriander</strong> (reserve a few leaves for garnish!), <strong>remaining chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>ginger paste </strong>and <strong>chopped chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to a <strong>food processor</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>cumin seeds</strong> and the juice of the <strong>remaining lime</strong> <strong>half[ves] </strong>with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and blitz until a sauce remains – this is your <strong>green chilli sauce</strong></p>",
